# Repair Debug UI Rule

- UI current node must follow IT Jump semantics: display and highlight `NEXT_STATION`.
- Main line diagram only renders route segment from `AOI_FIN_ASSY` to `T_VI`.
- If current logical node is at or after `T_VI`, show an `ALL PASS` message.
- Use three UI modes:
  - `main_line`
  - `repair_dido` (DI/DO/RI/RO/R_xxx display chain)
  - `repair_r_only` (R_xxx branch buttons with RC500/RC36 behavior)
- Pass action must support jump without mandatory user reason.
- Fail flow must:
  - load EC history from `R_REPAIR_T`
  - validate EC using `REPLACE(ERROR_CODE, ' ', '')` with error types `E/W`
  - call `SFIS1.NEW_TEST_INPUT_Z`
  - commit only when returned `RES='OK'`, otherwise rollback
- Employee ID source is top Search area and defaults to `SJOP`.
